We looked at commands such as "pwd" to know the location of the current directory,  "ls" to list all the files and folders in the current directory,  "cd " to navigate from current directory to the sub directory specified by the directory name field in the command, "cd .." to go to the immediate parent directory, "shutdown now" to shutdown the computer, "mkdir " to make a directory with the name specified by the directory name in the command, "touch " to create a file with the filename as described in the command, "ls -l" to list files in a directory with some extra information specified about those files such as size, etc. ]]></wp:meta_value>
